1. Open a web browser and navigate to your Google account.
2. Choose the Security option.
3. Within the "How you sign in to Google" section, opt for 2-Step Verification.
4. Scroll down to locate and click on App passwords.
5. Provide a descriptive name that will help you recall where you intend to use this app password.
6. Hit the Create button.
7. To utilize the app password, access the Google Account settings within your email client and substitute your regular password with the newly generated 16-character password.
8. Upon completing the process, revisit the App passwords page and click on Done.